BDI(AI Model Analysis)

Analysis

  • Model is a result of self-developed AI algorithm based on 5 variables including self-developed external environmental factors and strategic factors.

  • As a result of the analysis, the price fluctuation is properly predicted except for the level difference between June 2016 and October 2016 and 2017 (2015.01 ~ 2020.06, model accuracy is about 80.1%) It is analyzed that fluctuations in oil prices among external environmental factors affect prices after about a month.

  • From December 2019 to February 2020, it is analyzed that it had been recovered in about 3 months (May 2020) after the price drop due to COVID-19.

  • In the future, it is analyzed that additional market analysis and variable discovery (factors and events) will be needed to improve the accuracy and predictability of the model.

    \(\ast\) Model accuracy = 1 – ( \(E\) (\(\sum\)(\(\frac{|Base Price − Predict Price|}{Base Price}\))) * 100% )
